about.description: A pure Python Levenshtein implementation that's not freaking GPL'd. Based off the Wikipedia code samples at http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Levenshtein_distance.
about.summary: A pure Python Levenshtein implementation that's not freaking GPL'd.

name: pylev
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "pylev" %}
{% set version = "1.3.0" %}
{% set file_ext = "tar.gz" %}
{% set hash_type = "sha256" %}
{% set hash_value = "063910098161199b81e453025653ec53556c1be7165a9b7c50be2f4d57eae1c3" %}

package:
  name: '{{ name|lower }}'
  version: '{{ version }}'

source:
  fn: '{{ name }}-{{ version }}.{{ file_ext }}'
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.{{ file_ext }}
  '{{ hash_type }}': '{{ hash_value }}'

build:
  noarch: python
  number: 0
  script: python -m pip install --no-deps --ignore-installed .

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python

test:
  imports:
    - pylev

about:
  home: http://github.com/toastdriven/pylev
  license: BSD
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: "A pure Python Levenshtein implementation that's not freaking GPL'd."
  description: "A pure Python Levenshtein implementation that's not freaking GPL'd. 
    Based off the Wikipedia code samples at http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Levenshtein_distance."
  doc_url: https://pypi.org/project/pylev/
  dev_url: https://github.com/toastdriven/pylev

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - nick-youngblut
    - johanneskoester
    - bgruening
    - daler
    - jdblischak
    - cbrueffer
